{"lemma":"نُور","slug":"نُور","root":"ن.#.ر","root_slug":"ن-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نُور","root":"نور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":43},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40721","n40725","n40726"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flower, to blossom"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to light, to radiate, to illuminate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shed light"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enlighten"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blossoms, blooms","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"light, ray of light, light beam","examples":[{"text":"الْقَمَرُ يُضِيءُ اللَّيْلَ بِنُورِهِ السَّاحِرِ.","english":"The moon illuminates the night with its enchanting light."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brightness, gleam, glow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"illumination"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lamp, light, lantern"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"headlight"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a unisex given name, Noor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Nawar, one of the tribes of Doms in Egypt","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Gypsies","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tramps, vagabonds","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The “light” noun is inherited from Proto-Semitic *nūr-."},"ipa":["/naw.wa.ra/","/nawr/","/nuːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40721","headword_ar":"نوّر","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", intrans., in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAra","text_ar":"اَنَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwru","text_ar":"النُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, in two places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw~r biAlfajori","text_ar":"نوّر بِالفَجْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed the prayer of daybreak when the dawn had become light"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) (tropical:)  or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the horizon had become bright:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyru Alfajori","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرُ الفَجْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an amplification. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst. from this verb, see below.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw~r","text_ar":"نوّر"},{"kind":"text","text":", trans. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAra","text_ar":"اَنَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwru","text_ar":"النُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. in three places.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw~r","text_ar":"نوّر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K.) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a tree. S, A, Msb, K, and a plant, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blossomed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowered it put forth its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawor","text_ar":"نَوْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAra","text_ar":"اَنَارَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowara","text_ar":"اَنْوَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) See also 4. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(seed-produce)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attained to maturity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [see an ex. in a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smw","text_ar":"سمو"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 3:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the inf. n. of the verb in this sense, has a pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaAwiyru","text_ar":"تَنَاوِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw~rhu","text_ar":"نوّرهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He smeared him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrap","text_ar":"نُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw~r *iraAEahu","text_ar":"نوّر ذِرَاعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanowiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْوِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pricked his fore-arm with a needle, and then sprinkled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawuwr","text_ar":"نَوُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", [q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n40725","headword_ar":"نَوْرٌ","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blossoms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K,) of a tree, and of a plant: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white blossoms"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the yellow being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zahorN","text_ar":"زَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) for they become white, and then become yellow: (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworapN","text_ar":"نَوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuw~aArN","text_ar":"نُوَّارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworN","text_ar":"نَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworN","text_ar":"نَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuw~aArN","text_ar":"نُوَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; (S, Msb;) [but the former is often used as a generic n., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of blossom"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flower:"},{"kind":"text","text":"though both are coll. gen. ns.;] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworapN","text_ar":"نَوْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworN","text_ar":"نَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorapN","text_ar":"تَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuw~aArapN","text_ar":"نُوَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuw~aArN","text_ar":"نُوَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, L:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworN","text_ar":"نَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaArN","text_ar":"اَنْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","S","L"]},{"entry_id":"n40726","headword_ar":"نُورٌ","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever it be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulomapN","text_ar":"ظُلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rays thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K:) accord to Z,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyaA='N","text_ar":"ضِيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dawo'N","text_ar":"ضَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn.] is more intense than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the Kur, x. 5, the sun is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DyA'","text_ar":"ضياء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the moon"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwr","text_ar":"نور"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DyA'","text_ar":"ضياء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is essential, but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwr","text_ar":"نور"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accidental"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) it is of two kinds, the light of the present world and that of the world to come; and the former is either perceived sensibly, by the eye, and this is what diffuses itself from luminous bodies, as the sun and moon and stars, and is mentioned in the Kur, x. 5, referred to above; or perceived by the eye of the intellect, and this is what diffuses itself of the divine lights, as the light of reason and the light of the Kur-án; of which divine light mention is made in the Kur, v., former part of verse 18, and xxiv., latter part of verse 35; and both of these in common are spoken of in the Kur, vi. 1 and xxxix. 69: that of the world to come is mentioned in the Kur in lvii. 12 [and lxvi. 8]: (B:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaArN","text_ar":"اَنْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyraAnN","text_ar":"نِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) the latter mentioned by Th: (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naworaAny~apN","text_ar":"نَوْرَانيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) As"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwr","text_ar":"نور"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a convenience of the pious in the present world and the world to come, it is said in the Kur, [lvii. 13,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AunoZuruwnaA naqotabiso mino nuwrikumo","text_ar":"اُنْظُرُونَا نَقْتَبِسْ مِنْ نُورِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wait ye for us that we may take of your light"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (B.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulamopN","text_ar":"ظُلَمْةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  It is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mohammad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) it is said by Aboo-Is-hak to be so applied in the Kur, v. 18. (T.) ―         -b3-  And That"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which manifests things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and shows to the eyes their true"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"real state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwr","text_ar":"النُّور"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied in the Kur, vii. 156, to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revelation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the Prophet brought."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwru","text_ar":"النُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also one of the names of God; meaning, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He by whose light the obscure in perception sees, and by whose guidance the erring is directed aright:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Manifest, by whom is every manifestation."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^all~`hu nuwru Als~am`waAti waA@loA^aroDi","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ نُورُ السَّمٰوَاتِ وَا@لْاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur, xxiv. 35,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is the enlightener of the heavens and of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN giyaAvunaA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ غِيَاثُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugiyvunaA","text_ar":"مُغِيثُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right director of the inhabitants of the heavens and of the inhabitants of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naArN","text_ar":"نَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last signification."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2866}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","M","A","K","TA","B","T"]}]}}